'''表情圖標百科'''（{{lang-en|Emojipedia}}）是一个[[表情圖標|表情圖標]]参考网站，记载了[[Unicode标准|Unicode标准]]中各个表情[[图标|图标]]的编码、含义、演变等信息。

网站同时也是[[Unicode联盟|Unicode联盟]]的一员<ref>{{cite web|title=The Unicode Consortium Members|url=https://www.unicode.org/consortium/members.html|publisher=The Unicode Consortium|accessdate=2018-08-27|archive-date=2017-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205185034/http://www.unicode.org/consortium/members.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，提供了Unicode网站上的部分彩色表情图标<ref>{{cite web|title=Emoji Images and Rights|url=https://www.unicode.org/emoji/images.html|publisher=The Unicode Consortium|accessdate=2018-08-27|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427040116/http://www.unicode.org/emoji/images.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==历史==
2013年，[[苹果公司|苹果公司]]在新发布的[[iOS_6|iOS 6]]中增加了若干表情图标，但没有说明哪些图标是新增的，使不少用户产生了疑惑。为此，{{tsl|en|Jeremy Burge}}创建了表情图标百科。考虑到表情图标的官方名称较为隐晦，用户只需搜索其特征即可找到相应的表情图标。<ref>{{cite news|author=Victoria Ibitoye|title=Novel search engine acts as a ‘Wikipedia for emojis’|newspaper=Hackney Gazette|date=2016-03-31|page=12}}</ref>

2014年，随着Unicode 7引入了一批表情图标，尤其是备受争议的[[豎中指|中指]]图标，网站的访问量迅速上升。2015年，Burge辞去工作，完全投入网站的运营中。这一年网站页面浏览量已达1.4亿。<ref>{{cite web|author=Rob Price|title=This 31-year-old Australian accidentally built a huge empire by cataloging all the world's emojis|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/emojipedia-jeremy-burge-emoji-encyclopedia-profile-2016-1|date=2016-01-17|accessdate=2018-08-28|publisher=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]]|archive-date=2016-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129010513/http://uk.businessinsider.com/emojipedia-jeremy-burge-emoji-encyclopedia-profile-2016-1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年9月，网站发起了认领表情图标活动，将站内的[[广告|广告]]替换为愿意认领表情的[[赞助商|赞助商]]的链接。但同年12月，[[Unicode联盟|Unicode联盟]]也发起了类似的认领[[字符|字符]]活动，为其工作募集资金<ref>{{cite web|title=Unicode Launches Adopt-a-Character Campaign to Support the World’s “Digitally Disadvantaged” Living Languages|url=http://blog.unicode.org/2015/12/unicode-launches-adopt-character.html|publisher=The Unicode Consortium|date=2015-12-16|accessdate=2018-08-28|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122192853/http://blog.unicode.org/2015/12/unicode-launches-adopt-character.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。为了支持Unicode联盟，防止混淆，2016年11月，网站的认领表情图标活动宣告结束。<ref>{{cite web|title=Adopt Your Emoji At Unicode|url=https://blog.emojipedia.org/adopt-your-emoji-at-unicode/|publisher=Emojipedia|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2018-08-28|archive-date=2021-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429224215/https://blog.emojipedia.org/adopt-your-emoji-at-unicode/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年，表情图标百科主张苹果公司不应将[[手枪|手枪]]图标改为[[水枪|水枪]]（🔫）<ref>{{cite web|author=Chris Baraniuk|title=Apple urged to rethink gun emoji change|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-36985359|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|date=2016-08-05|accessdate=2018-08-27|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111184059/https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-36985359|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但未获采纳。

2018年，[[滑板|滑板]]运动员[[Tony_Hawk|Tony Hawk]]指出，表情图标百科发布的滑板图标设计过时，并协助设计了新图标。同一批图标中的[[DNA|DNA]]和[[龙虾|龙虾]]图标也被指出不符合生物学构造，随后被修改。<ref>{{cite web|title=Skateboard, DNA and Lobster Updated|url=https://blog.emojipedia.org/skateboard-dna-and-lobster-updated/|publisher=Emojipedia|date=2018-02-19|accessdate=2018-08-28|archive-date=2021-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412121929/https://blog.emojipedia.org/skateboard-dna-and-lobster-updated/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==世界表情圖標日==
{{main|世界表情图标日}}
2014年，表情图标百科将每年的7月17日定为[[世界表情图标日|世界表情图标日]]，这是日历表情图标（📅）上显示的日期。<ref>{{cite news|author=Emma O'Neill Deighan|title=It’s World Emoji Day, how will you celebrate?|url=https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/incoming/its-world-emoji-day-how-9680218|date=2015-07-17|accessdate=2018-08-27|publisher=Belfast Live|archive-date=2020-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102191359/https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/incoming/its-world-emoji-day-how-9680218|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Amanda Schupak|title=Could you use these new emoji in a sentence?|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/could-you-use-these-new-emoji-in-a-sentence/|date=2015-07-17|accessdate=2018-08-27|publisher=[[CBS_News|CBS News]]|archive-date=2019-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191201054758/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/could-you-use-these-new-emoji-in-a-sentence/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Kathryn Varn|title=Letting Our Emojis Get in the Way|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/18/nytnow/letting-our-emojis-get-in-the-way.html|date=2015-07-17|accessdate=2018-08-27|publisher=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308140250/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/18/nytnow/letting-our-emojis-get-in-the-way.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

